01:34:15.776 --> 01:34:19.404
If you give me your ring,
and I win tomorrow,

01:34:20.906 --> 01:34:23.158
I'll let you have sex with me.

01:34:23.826 --> 01:34:25.577
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

01:34:28.497 --> 01:34:29.998
<i>(SCREAMS)</i>

01:34:40.843 --> 01:34:43.428
<i>MAN ON TV: ...has left Rocky wondering
where the others have gone.</i>

01:34:43.512 --> 01:34:46.014
<i>His old anxieties
about being left alone...</i>

01:34:46.098 --> 01:34:49.434
<i>WOMAN ON TV: Now there's an easy
way to remember everything.</i>

01:34:49.518 --> 01:34:51.311
<i>Oh, thank you, Mike.</i>

01:34:51.895 --> 01:34:54.231
<i>I'll buy you a better one,
just as soon as I...</i>

01:34:54.314 --> 01:34:55.607
<i>No, you won't.</i>

01:34:55.691 --> 01:34:58.110
<i>I'm always going to keep this one.</i>

01:34:58.235 --> 01:34:59.945
<i>I'll never part with it.</i>

01:35:00.028 --> 01:35:01.822
<i>Never, never, never.</i>

01:35:07.828 --> 01:35:10.914
<i>Let's do it properly. Please.</i>

01:35:30.100 --> 01:35:31.810
(PEOPLE CHEERING)

01:35:39.985 --> 01:35:42.613
PHOTOGRAPHER:
Ms. Maes. Over here. Smile!

01:35:44.197 --> 01:35:45.824
Thank you, Sophie.

01:35:49.870 --> 01:35:51.914
What people don't realise
is that all saints start out

01:35:51.997 --> 01:35:53.415
as human beings.

01:35:53.498 --> 01:35:56.585
And all human beings fall in love
at some point, right?

01:35:56.668 --> 01:35:59.421
- Mother Teresa still has...
- It's really important, sure.

01:35:59.504 --> 01:36:01.006
Well, anyway...

01:36:06.011 --> 01:36:08.513
MADDOX: Well, well. Look at you.

01:36:10.140 --> 01:36:13.435
Made it all the way to the seventh room.
Congratulations.

01:36:13.518 --> 01:36:16.521
Wheel of fortune, right?
You go up, I go down.

01:36:17.522 --> 01:36:19.775
You here with Sophie?
How about doing your old rabbi a favour

01:36:19.858 --> 01:36:21.443
and putting in a good word for me?

01:36:21.526 --> 01:36:23.070
- Need a little interview.
- Is Alison here?

01:36:23.153 --> 01:36:25.864
Alison? No.
We went our separate ways.

01:36:26.573 --> 01:36:27.824
Actually, she left me.

01:36:27.908 --> 01:36:30.661
And tells me she's in love
with someone else.

01:36:31.787 --> 01:36:37.042
Nope. Not you, I'm afraid, Sidalee.
Some guy named Clark.

01:36:37.376 --> 01:36:40.754
Can you believe it?
These are the sacrifices we make.

01:36:41.463 --> 01:36:45.467
I don't need to tell you.
This isn't a vacation, it's a vocation.

01:36:45.717 --> 01:36:49.638
So, listen. About Sophie, need
a little interview. It won't take long.

01:36:50.722 --> 01:36:52.557
(PEOPLE APPLAUDING)

01:36:56.728 --> 01:36:59.564
<i>SIDNEY: So, here I am
at the centre of everything.</i>

01:37:00.357 --> 01:37:03.777
<i>I've got the tux, I've got the watch,
I've got the life.</i>

01:37:04.069 --> 01:37:06.321
<i>I am exactly where I wanted to be.</i>

01:37:06.405 --> 01:37:07.990
(INAUDIBLE)

01:37:09.700 --> 01:37:12.160
<i>I've made it to Shangri-la.</i>

01:37:12.619 --> 01:37:14.246
(CHEERING)

01:37:32.222 --> 01:37:33.348
I'm gonna have to
have the ring back, okay?

01:37:33.432 --> 01:37:34.391
What are you doing?

01:37:34.474 --> 01:37:36.518
- I need you to give me the ring.
- Get away from me.

01:37:36.601 --> 01:37:38.061
- What are you doing?
- Give me the ring back.

01:37:38.145 --> 01:37:40.272
My mother gave me this ring,
and she told me to give it to the one.

01:37:40.355 --> 01:37:41.982
- She's not the one!
- Have you lost your mind?

01:37:42.065 --> 01:37:43.275
- No, just... Will you just...
- Let me go.

01:37:43.358 --> 01:37:45.902
I don't want to be on the inside!
I don't want to be at the party!

01:37:45.986 --> 01:37:48.030
I don't want to have sex with you!

01:37:48.113 --> 01:37:49.698
I killed Cuba!

01:37:49.781 --> 01:37:51.074
(ALL GASP)

01:37:52.242 --> 01:37:53.618
(GROWLING)

01:38:00.042 --> 01:38:01.668
No. Hey!

01:38:02.961 --> 01:38:05.839
Fucking, mother-fucking fucker!

01:38:06.506 --> 01:38:07.632
God!

01:38:08.258 --> 01:38:09.426
Stop it!

01:38:09.509 --> 01:38:12.054
SIDNEY: This is live!
SOPHIE: I don't care!

01:38:12.971 --> 01:38:14.806
<i>ANNOUNCER: Well,
this is a strange one.</i>

01:38:14.890 --> 01:38:17.642
<i>We've certainly never seen anything
quite like this before</i>

01:38:17.726 --> 01:38:19.770
<i>at the Apollo Film Awards.</i>

01:38:23.231 --> 01:38:25.942
Sodom and Gomorrah!

01:38:26.151 --> 01:38:27.444
<i>I'm sorry!</i>

01:38:28.236 --> 01:38:29.321
(ALL GASP)

01:38:29.404 --> 01:38:31.573
<i>ANNOUNCER: I've just been informed
that the young man involved</i>

01:38:31.656 --> 01:38:32.741
<i>in the altercation</i>

01:38:32.824 --> 01:38:36.286
<i>is Sidney Young,
a reporter with</i> Sharps <i>magazine.</i>

01:38:42.918 --> 01:38:45.087
ELEANOR: Take your hands off of me!

01:38:45.170 --> 01:38:47.756
You are finished! You're finished!

01:38:50.717 --> 01:38:52.594
- Hey, Vincent.
- Sidney.

01:38:57.808 --> 01:38:58.892
Fuck.

01:38:58.975 --> 01:38:59.976
(GROANS)

01:39:04.981 --> 01:39:05.982
(LAUGHS)

01:39:17.869 --> 01:39:19.329
(SIDNEY PANTING)

01:39:37.889 --> 01:39:39.141
Have a nice flight.

01:39:39.224 --> 01:39:41.393
I need a ticket to New York, please.

01:39:45.564 --> 01:39:48.984
The next available flight isn't
until tomorrow morning at 10:00.

01:39:49.067 --> 01:39:51.736
It arrives in New York at 6:30 p.m.
local time.

01:39:51.987 --> 01:39:53.822
There's nothing sooner?

01:39:53.905 --> 01:39:56.700
- No, I'm afraid not.
- Fine. I'll take it.

01:39:57.909 --> 01:40:00.912
<i>Hi, you've reached Alison.
Please leave a message.</i>

01:40:00.996 --> 01:40:04.207
<i>Oh, and Joe, if that's you, I got
the tickets for Empire Park tomorrow.</i>

01:40:04.291 --> 01:40:06.293
<i>I'll see you there. Bye.</i>

01:40:06.877 --> 01:40:08.170
Alison, it's me. It's Sidney.

01:40:08.253 --> 01:40:11.089
Listen, my battery is very low,
and I wanted to...

01:40:11.464 --> 01:40:13.425
Can I see you? I just...

01:40:13.508 --> 01:40:15.927
I don't think I'm going to be working
for <i>Sharps</i> any more, okay?

01:40:16.011 --> 01:40:19.181
But it's fine.
Because I thought I wanted all that stuff.

01:40:19.389 --> 01:40:21.016
I thought I wanted to be special
and have the money

01:40:21.099 --> 01:40:23.310
and be treated differently
to everybody else.

01:40:23.393 --> 01:40:25.187
Can I get an upgrade?

01:40:25.520 --> 01:40:28.023
But I don't, okay? And... Who's Joe?

01:40:28.106 --> 01:40:29.524
(CELL PHONE BEEPS)

01:40:29.941 --> 01:40:31.193
(SIGHS)

01:40:44.456 --> 01:40:46.583
Could I get your autograph?

01:40:47.209 --> 01:40:49.044
What? 'Cause I'm on the TV?

01:40:49.127 --> 01:40:51.546
'Cause I'm up there
close to the movie stars?

01:40:51.630 --> 01:40:52.797
'Cause you think I'm special?

01:40:52.881 --> 01:40:54.716
For your credit card?

01:40:56.801 --> 01:40:57.844
Yes.

01:41:00.347 --> 01:41:02.307
Do you have any baggage?

01:41:02.849 --> 01:41:04.059
Plenty.

01:41:09.231 --> 01:41:12.025
<i>(ENOUGH LOVE</i> PLAYING)

01:42:05.245 --> 01:42:07.706
Stop the car. Stop the car! Stop the car!

01:42:32.731 --> 01:42:34.983
(MOVIE PLAYING)

01:43:00.592 --> 01:43:01.634
Hi.

01:43:03.762 --> 01:43:04.763
Hi.

01:43:08.266 --> 01:43:10.477
How's the novel coming along?

01:43:13.146 --> 01:43:14.689
It's finished.

01:43:18.276 --> 01:43:20.195
Thanks for the ending.

01:43:59.442 --> 01:44:01.361
<i>(LA DOLCE VITA FINALE</i> PLAYING)

01:44:37.147 --> 01:44:38.440
Oh, fuck!

01:44:41.359 --> 01:44:42.569
<i>(YOU REALLY GOT ME</i> PLAYING)

01:45:53.598 --> 01:45:56.726
Mother Superior? This is Agnes
from the Ottoman Empire.

01:45:56.809 --> 01:45:59.771
<i>ANNOUNCER: Sometimes,
before you can find belief,</i>

01:46:01.105 --> 01:46:04.192
<i>you have to find someone
who will believe in you.</i>

01:46:04.275 --> 01:46:07.904
<i>WOMAN: They say you travelled alone.
You came by train?</i>

01:46:07.987 --> 01:46:09.197
<i>By foot.</i>

01:46:09.280 --> 01:46:12.325
That is not a suitable way
for a young lady to travel.

01:46:12.825 --> 01:46:14.702
It is how the poor must travel.

01:46:14.786 --> 01:46:17.539
<i>ANNOUNCER: Sometimes,
what is so wrong...</i>

01:46:17.622 --> 01:46:18.790
MAN: You left this.

01:46:18.873 --> 01:46:20.917
<i>ANNOUNCER: ...can feel so right.</i>

01:46:21.459 --> 01:46:22.418
Stop it!

01:46:22.502 --> 01:46:24.587
<i>WOMAN: You've given
yourself to Christ.</i>

01:46:24.671 --> 01:46:28.424
(SOBS) But I love him.
How can it be wrong?

01:46:29.634 --> 01:46:30.718
<i>Why?</i>

01:46:30.802 --> 01:46:33.805
<i>- I was told to come here.
- Who told you?</i>

01:46:36.808 --> 01:46:37.934
God.

01:46:38.476 --> 01:46:42.063
<i>WOMAN: The faith is strong in this one.</i>

01:46:42.146 --> 01:46:44.440
<i>I believe in love. That is all we have,</i>

01:46:44.524 --> 01:46:47.360
<i>and we must give it
wherever it is most needed.</i>

01:46:47.527 --> 01:46:48.570
Calcutta.

01:46:48.653 --> 01:46:53.283
<i>ANNOUNCER: Sometimes, before you
can find God, you have to find yourself.</i>

01:46:53.366 --> 01:46:55.910
Stand up, Mother Teresa.

01:46:55.994 --> 01:47:00.123
<i>ANNOUNCER: In a world where passion
is forbidden and belief is divine,</i>

01:47:00.206 --> 01:47:02.250
<i>one woman achieved everything</i>

01:47:02.333 --> 01:47:05.128
<i>by helping those who had nothing.</i>

01:47:06.170 --> 01:47:09.757
<i>Sir Ben Queensley,
Dame Peggy Aitken,</i>

01:47:09.841 --> 01:47:13.094
<i>Tod Rivera,
and introducing Sophie Maes.</i>

01:47:13.177 --> 01:47:15.305
Teresa, The Making of a Saint.

01:47:16.764 --> 01:47:18.683
<i>A Mel Cohen Film. Rated NC-17.</i>

